msgstr ""

#: inc/customizer.php:343
msgid "Subscriber count"
msgstr ""

#: inc/customizer.php:344
msgid "Shown as “Join 48,000 readers”. Leave empty to hide the line — an honest empty is better than an invented number."
msgstr ""

#: inc/customizer.php:353
msgid "Form endpoint"
msgstr ""

#: inc/customizer.php:354
msgid "Where the signup form posts. Broadside stores no subscribers and sends no mail — it renders the form and hands the address to whatever service you name here (a webhook, an automation, a mailing-list provider). Leave empty and the form is not rendered at all."
msgstr ""

#: inc/customizer.php:362
msgid "Email field name"
msgstr ""

#: inc/customizer.php:363
msgid "The name attribute of the email input. Whatever your endpoint expects — most want “email”."
msgstr ""

#: inc/customizer.php:377
msgid "Drop cap on the opening paragraph"
msgstr ""

#: inc/customizer.php:378
msgid "Applied automatically to the first paragraph of every article."
msgstr ""

#: inc/customizer.php:386
msgid "Show reading time"
msgstr ""

#: inc/customizer.php:387
msgid "Estimated from the word count at 220 words a minute."
msgstr ""

#: inc/customizer.php:395
msgid "Editorial standards note"
msgstr ""

#: inc/customizer.php:396
msgid "Printed in small italics at the foot of every article, above the related stories. A good place for your fact-checking policy, an age warning, or a link to your ethics page. Basic links and emphasis are allowed. Leave empty to omit it."
msgstr ""

#: inc/customizer.php:449
